                        <p />
                        <h2>Adult Education: Tuesday, September 24</h2>
                        <div class="article"><p>
                        <span style="font-weight: bold;">Kol Hadash Office<br />
	
	<a href="https://maps.google.com/maps?oe=utf-8&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;q=175+Olde+Half+Day+Road&amp;ie=UTF-8&amp;hq=&amp;hnear=0x880fbe0a5003074f:0x53ca5eb5755a7cac,175+Olde+Half+Day+Rd,+Lincolnshire,+IL+60069&amp;gl=us&amp;ei=Z6D-UZ6VJtGgrgHOloG4AQ&amp;ved=0CC8Q8gEwAA">175 Olde Half Day Road, Lincolnshire IL</a><br />
	
	7:30 PM<br />
	
	</span><br />
<span style="font-weight: bold;">High Holidays &amp; Major Festivals</span><br />
Did you know that the names <span style="font-style: italic;">Rosh Hashana </span>and<span style="font-style: italic;"> Yom Kippur</span> do not appear in the Torah? Or that Passover was originally two holidays that were later combined into one? Join us for the history behind these and other important holidays in the Jewish calendar. <br />
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic;">This
 session is part of Rabbi Chalom's yearlong Jewish Culture &amp; 
Philosophy Adult Education course, focusing on Jewish Culture in the 
first half of the 2013-14 year and then focusing on Jewish Philosophy. 
Members are invited to attend one class, a few, or all. There is no 
charge...all are welcome!<br />
	
</span><br />

<br />


                        </p></div>

                        
                        

